<div class="news-item">
    <h3 style="margin-top: 0">History &amp; Background</h3>
    <p>
        The Nspire CX line is TI's top-of-the-line series, replacing the Nspire and 89 lines. Notably,
        unlike Casio's (ClassPads) and HP's (Primes) lines, the Nspire does not have a touchscreen of either
        type; instead the CX series' D-pad doubles as a trackpad which is used to manipulate a mouse.
    </p>
</div>

